    "congress": 119,
    "constitutionalAuthorityStatementText": "<pre>\n[Congressional Record Volume 171, Number 1 (Friday, January 3, 2025)]\n[House]\n[Pages H36-H37]\nFrom the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href=\"https://www.gpo.gov\">www.gpo.gov</a>]\nBy Ms. PRESSLEY:\nH.R. 40.\nCongress has the power to enact this legislation pursuant\nto the following:\nPursuant to Section 5 of the Fourteenth Amendment to the\nUnited States Constitution, Congress shall have the power to\nenact appropriate laws protecting the civil rights of all\nAmericans\n[[Page H37]]\nThe single subject of this legislation is:\nTo address the fundamental injustice, cruelty, brutality,\nand inhumanity of slavery in the United States\n</pre>",
